subSection.paragraph:
Osteoporosis is a systemic bone disease characterised by reduced bone mass, impaired bone quality, and decreased bone strength, which causes bone fragility and fracture (
Foger-Samwald et al., 2020
). Osteoporosis is a common disease among older women (
Johnston and Dagar, 2020
); indeed, one third of women over the age of 50 will suffer from osteoporosis (
Kanis et al., 2000
). owing to its insidious onset, symptoms of osteoporosis do not manifest until the fracture occurs, thus posing a serious threat to women’ s health (
Johnston and Dagar, 2020
). Osteoporosis is associated with decreased estrogen levels in postmenopausal women (
Bado et al., 2017
). Estrogen plays important roles in bone resorption and formation in many ways (
Khosla et al., 2012
). It activates the Wnt/β- catenin signalling pathway, which promotes the differentiation and maturation of bone marrow mesenchymal stem cells (BMSCs) into osteoblasts (
Almeida et al., 2017
; 
Bado et al., 2017
). Moreover, estrogen inhibits the levels of osteoclast differentiation factors IL-1, IL-6, IL-7, and TNF-α, and induces osteoclast apoptosis through the Fasl pathway (
Khalid and Krum, 2016
). And estrogen affects differentiation by regulating the ratio of RANKL/OPG (
Noh et al., 2020
). Therefore, estrogen replacement therapy (ERT) is the preferred treatment for early menopause. ERT supplements help relieve menopause-associated symptoms, but simultaneously bring some adverse effects, such as the increasing risk of breast cancer and stroke (
Harper-Harrison and Shanahan, 2021
). For this reason, researchers are committed to seeking estrogen substitutes, among which phytoestrogen (PE), a mild estrogen analogue, has become a research hotspot (
Petrine and Del Bianco-Borges, 2021
).

The mature fruit of 

Psoralea corylifolia

L. (Leguminosae) is a common traditional Chinese medicine (TCM) used to tonify the kidney and yang, and to treat colitis, pollakiuria, osteoporosis, eczema and leucoderma (
Koul et al., 2019
). It is also used as a natural food additive (
Chino et al., 2002
). Kidney-tonifying TCM is used for the treatment of osteoporosis, based on the TCM theory that bone growth depends on the nourishment of kidney essence (
An et al., 2016
). PE from fruits of 

P. corylifolia

. is the material basis for anti-osteoporosis. For example, psoralidin promotes osteogenesis and inhibits the adipogenesis of BMSCs, while suppressing bone loss in ovariectomised rats (
Cao et al., 2019
; 
Zhai et al., 2018
). Meanwhile neobavaisoflavone inhibits osteoclastogenesis, promotes osteogenesis, and ameliorates bone loss in ovariectomised mice (
Chen et al., 2020
).

With the aim of identifying the anti-osteoporosis constituents of 

P. corylifolia

, a systematic phytochemical study was carried out. Plant material (
47.9 kg
) was extracted with 70% ethanol. The crude extract was partitioned successively with cyclohexane (cHe), ethyl acetate (EtOAc), and normal butanol (
n
-BuOH). The EtOAc extract was separated using various column chromatography methods. Fortunately, diverse structures were obtained. In our previous study, four flavonones and chalcones (
Xu et al., 2018
), 17 heterodimers of meroterpene phenol (
Xu et al., 2020b
), and 22 meroterpene phenols (
Xu et al., 2020a
) were identified. In this study, we report a further109 compounds (
1–109
) (
Fig. S1
), containing 37 undescribed compounds (1–6, 18–33, 53–60, 74–75, 94, 103–105, 106) (
Fig. 1
). The identified compounds included 17 coumarins (
1–17
), 35 isoflavones (18–52), 21 flavonones (53–73), 20 chalcones (74–93), 6 flavones (94–99), 3 benzofurans (
100–102
), 3 chromones (
103–105
), 2 isoflavanols (106 and 107), and 2 glycosides (108 and 109). Herein, the structures of undescribed compounds were elucidated and the structures of some coumarins (
7–10
) were corrected.

Estrogen binding to ER alpha and beta (ERα and ERβ), plays a key role in bone metabolism (
Khalid and Krum, 2016
). The expression of ERβ in bone tissue is higher than that of ERα (
Bado et al., 2017
; 
Liu et al., 2020
). Consequently, in order to explain their SAR in depth, we evaluated the binding affinities of eight compounds and ERβ by SPR technology. The affinity values of the eight compounds and ERβ were shown in 
Fig. 6
. The KD values of most compounds were analyzed using a kinetic model, whereas the KD values of E2, neobavaisoflavone (
42
) and neocorylin (
37
) were obtained using the affinity model. For two coumarins, psoralidin (
13
) (12.4 
μ
M) exhibited a stronger affinity than coumestrol (
11
) (25.0 
μ
M). When it comes to six isoflavones, the KD values of 3 
′
-methoxydaidzein (
46
) and neobavaisoflavone (
42
) were 8.81 and 7.28 
μ
M respectively, indicating stronger affinities than that of daidzein (
44
) (28 
μ
M). In contrast, the affinities of corylifol A (
49
) (54.4 
μ
M), neocorylin (
37
) (96.1 
μ
M) and bakuisoflavone (
47
) (92.8 
μ
M) were weaker than that of daidzein (
44
). Remarkably, compared with E2 (13.9 
μ
M), psoralidin (
13
), neobavaisofalvone (
42
), and 3 
′
-methoxydaidzein (
46
) showed better affinities. The above-mentioned results showed that compounds with an intact isopentenyl replacement possessed a stronger affinity for ERβ than the compounds without isopentenyl substitution or compounds with altered isopentenyl group. Moreover, when a methoxyl group was introduced on C-3 
′
of daidzein, the compound also exhibited a better affinity than daidzein (
44
). Based on the above-mentioned reasons, psoralidin (
13
), neobavaisofalvone (
42
) and 3 
′
-methoxydaidzein (
46
) showed improved results at the cellular level.

Based on the traditional role of 

P. corylifolia

in the treatment of osteoporosis, 89 library constituents were evaluated for their osteogenic differentiation and mineralisation activities of MC3T3-E1 cells, to identify potentially active compounds and investigate their SAR. We found that coumarins, isoflavones, flavonones and meroterpenoids were the basis for the role of 

P. corylifolia

in osteoporosis treatment. Among these constituents, psoralen (
16
), isopsoralen (
17
), coumestrol (
11
), psoralidin (
13
), daidzein (
44
), 3 
′
-methoxydaidzein (
46
), neobavaisoflavone (
42
), corylifol A (
49
), neocorylin (
37
), bavachin (
110
), bavachinin (
111
), bakuchiol (
114
), 12-oxobakuchiol (
118
), corypsoriol A (
121
), genistin (
108
) and astragaline (
109
) exhibited excellent activities. The activities of the representative compounds, psoralidin (
13
) and neobavaisoflavone (
42
), were decreased by the ER antagonist ICI, indicating that these compounds functioned via the ER pathway and were natural PE. Therefore, these compounds could serve as potential drugs or health foods for relieving menopausal symptoms and for the treatment of postmenopausal osteoporosis.

